  "body": "For v9.2 of the phase 0 beacon chain, I am assuming that we calculate the max number of validators as follows: \r\n\r\n`MAX_VALIDATORS_PER_COMMITTEE` * `MAX_COMMITTEES_PER_SLOT` = 2^11 * 2^6 = 2^17 \r\n\r\nif so, then this function:\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef get_validator_churn_limit(state: BeaconState) -> uint64:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Return the validator churn limit for the current epoch.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    active_validator_indices = get_active_validator_indices(state, get_current_epoch(state))\r\n    return max(MIN_PER_EPOCH_CHURN_LIMIT, len(active_validator_indices) // CHURN_LIMIT_QUOTIENT)\r\n```\r\nwill always be equal to `MIN_PER_EPOCH_CHURN_LIMIT`.",
